    <item>
      <title>Lazy Sad Snow - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/20/lazy-sad-snow/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/20/lazy-sad-snow/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Dec 2024 02:13:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7842" class="post-7842 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Lazy Sad Snow&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Drift was talking about the snow being lazy and loafing around.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drift-lazy1-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Snow is so lazy! It's disgusting! Look at it, loafin' around like that!" class="wp-image-7843" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Then he said it reminds him of me! How rude!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drift-lazy2-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Kinda reminds me of you, rrrrribbit!" class="wp-image-7844" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline then told me to watch out for girls who have a lot of flowers in their gardens!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/caroline-garden1-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: You know, if you meet a girl with lots of flowers in her garden..." class="wp-image-7850" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She warned me never to trust a green thumb! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/caroline-garden2-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: You'd better watch out for her! She's up to no good! Never trust a green thumb!" class="wp-image-7851" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Filbert told me that he was pretty indifferent towards Bones and Curt. But then when I (immediately) spoke to him again, he suddenly had an urgent delivery for Curt!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/filbert-urgent-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: Well, I have an urgent delivery for Curt..." class="wp-image-7845" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Why would he be sending a gift to Curt (let alone an &amp;#8220;urgent&amp;#8221; one) when he feels indifferent towards him? 😛 But I took the gift (a five-ball shirt) over to Curt, and he was impressed by it. Filbert then rewarded me with 510 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Truffles said that seeing all the snow around makes her sad&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/truffles-snow-150x112.jpg" alt="Truffles: Y'know, when I see all this snow lying around, it makes me, like, kinda sad..." class="wp-image-7847" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But not for a reason I&amp;#8217;d expect. She&amp;#8217;s sad because she thinks it&amp;#8217;s going to be gone in a few days! &lt;strong&gt;Ha!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/truffles-gone-150x112.jpg" alt="Truffles: Why? Because it's gonna be GONE in a few days!!" class="wp-image-7848" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You sweet summer child. We still have over two months of it to go.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Over at town hall, I found an arctic camo (shirt) in the recycle bin. I also put some money into my savings account, and my balance reached 14 million bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/14m-150x112.jpg" alt="Pelly: The current bell balance is 14,000,000." class="wp-image-7849" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/20/lazy-sad-snow/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2024-12-20T21:13:27-05:00"&gt;December 20, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drift-lazy1.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Aurora&amp;#039;s Coconut Cake - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/12/17/auroras-coconut-cake/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/12/17/auroras-coconut-cake/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 04:37:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18063" class="post-18063 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Aurora&amp;#8217;s Coconut Cake&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On December 4th, I shot down a balloon present! Ooh, what could be inside?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241204_HNI_0002-250x150.jpg" alt="Shooting down a balloon present as Inkwell looks on." class="wp-image-18064" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Inside, I found a milk can. That was a milky way of spoiling my excitement. 🥛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mira was describing someone with two horns, brown fur, and a strong profile&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241204_HNI_0007-250x150.jpg" alt="Mira: He's got two horns, fluffy, brown fur, and a strong profile..." class="wp-image-18065" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She was talking about Jingle, of course.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241204_HNI_0008-250x150.jpg" alt="Mira: You know, when you put it into words like that, Jingle sounds like a real weirdo! I hopped!" class="wp-image-18066" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I think you just put yourself on the naughty list.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Now that December is here, villagers have started to give hints about what they want for Toy Day. I&amp;#8217;m going to list the hints I&amp;#8217;ve received so far, although it isn&amp;#8217;t many:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Cube: something aqua&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Inkwell: white furniture&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Mira: black appliance&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I probably need to speak more to the villagers who I&amp;#8217;m &lt;em&gt;not &lt;/em&gt;focused on getting photos from. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On December 5th, Inkwell asked for some furniture to replace his cupid bench. I checked Re-Tail, the lost and found, T&amp;amp;T Emporium, and Harv&amp;#8217;s shop, but I couldn&amp;#8217;t find any rectangular furniture. But when I checked my museum exhibit rooms, I found a Kiki and Lala sofa I wasn&amp;#8217;t using. I gave it to Inkwell, and he loved it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241205_HNI_0030-250x150.jpg" alt="Inkwell: Wow! A Kiki and Lala sofa! It's perfect!" class="wp-image-18067" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In return, he just gave me the Cupid bench. Not bad, but it&amp;#8217;s still not his photo.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I played again on Sunday (the 15th), I saw that snow now covers the ground and festive lights adorn many trees. 🎄 The holidays are getting close!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241215_HNI_0036-250x150.jpg" alt="Festive lights on trees between Re-Tail and the waterfall." class="wp-image-18068" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Molly was sitting on the metal bench in town. She asked me to join her for a bit, so I did! Molly is always so cute. 🙂&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0044-250x150.jpg" alt="Sitting on the metal bench with Molly." class="wp-image-18069" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Jeremiah told me he needed Aurora for something, and he asked if I would go and get her. He said he was too tired to do it himself.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0045-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: the thing is, I'm super sleepy right now and would probably fall right over if I tried to leave the house." class="wp-image-18070" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I agreed to fetch Aurora, but first, I ran into Lolly. She asked me to bury a time capsule for her&amp;#8230;so I did that too.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0047-250x150.jpg" alt="Lolly: sorry to spring this on you, but would you be interested in burying my time capsule for me?" class="wp-image-18071" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I ultimately found Aurora by the flower clock, just outside of town hall.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0052-250x150.jpg" alt="Aurora stands by the flower clock in Animal Crossing: New Leaf (ACNL) for Nintendo 3DS." class="wp-image-18072" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I told her the news, and we headed over to Jeremiah&amp;#8217;s house. Jeremiah just wanted to know if he could have some of the coconut cake he smelled her cooking yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0054-250x150.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: I was walking by your house yesterday, Aurora, and I caught a whiff of some coconut cake." class="wp-image-18073" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Aurora didn&amp;#8217;t appreciate the fact that Jeremiah was lurking around her house. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0056-250x150.jpg" alt="Aurora: Huh?! You were lurking around my house to spy on my snacks? That'd be creepy if it weren't so sad." class="wp-image-18074" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But she said she couldn&amp;#8217;t share the cake anyway, because she already ate it all!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241217_HNI_0057-250x150.jpg" alt="Aurora: Anyway, I can't share with you, because I've eaten everything." class="wp-image-18075" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then stormed out of his house. Jeremiah was going to give me a reward, but my pockets were full. So he said he&amp;#8217;ll mail it instead.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m not sure if I&amp;#8217;ll play on Toy Day (Christmas Eve) this year or not. It may depend on whether I get enough gift hints before then. But regardless, I will be back at some point later this month with another entry. I&amp;#8217;ll see you then. Happy holidays!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/12/17/auroras-coconut-cake/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2024-12-17T23:37:30-05:00"&gt;December 17, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241204_HNI_0002.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Snow Reactions - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2024/12/16/snow-reactions/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2024/12/16/snow-reactions/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 17 Dec 2024 00:06:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5865" class="post-5865 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Snow Reactions&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;As of last Wednesday, snow now covers the ground in Animal Crossing. Unfortunately, I received Peanut&amp;#8217;s goodbye letter in the mail. I was hoping she&amp;#8217;d stick around longer, but she has already split.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-peanut2024-gone-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Jeff! I woke the other day with wanderlust, so I just up and left. Wild, huh? On the road, destination unknown! Anyway, thanks for dealing with my craziness! Cheery-bye! -Peanut" class="wp-image-5866" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In addition to the snow, there are also festive lights on many non-fruit trees. (That includes cedar trees too, although none of those happen to be in this screenshot.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-holiday2024-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Festive lights on trees for the holidays in Animal Crossing." class="wp-image-5867" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with Buzz, he told me he never sees my face these days. But as he was saying it, I actually spotted a &lt;em&gt;different &lt;/em&gt;face watching us from behind the tree! Look closely, and you can see it here:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-buzz-face-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Buzz: I never see your face at all these days." class="wp-image-5868" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later met Peanut&amp;#8217;s replacement, Marcy the kangaroo. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-marcy2024-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Marcy: My name is Marcy! Isn't it a cute name, young 'un? Yeah... I know it is." class="wp-image-5869" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She lived in Forest before, back in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2012/06/03/summer-camper-and-fishing-tournament/"&gt;2012&lt;/a&gt;. But I also have her in my town of Aja Blu, as you may have seen in my GameCube Moments #22 video from a couple weeks ago. If you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it, here it is:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing - GameCube Moments #22" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/52d8-p1nKmU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, I found Gulliver down on the beach. After rambling for a bit, he gave me a stone coin&amp;#8230;as a &lt;em&gt;token &lt;/em&gt;of his appreciation.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-gulliver-token-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Gulliver: Hmm? Oh! I see! You wanted a TOKEN of my thanks! Well, BWAHAHAHA!" class="wp-image-5870" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I played again tonight, and it was snowing in town. Candi wondered if I was scared of the snow because she didn&amp;#8217;t see me during the day.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-candi-scared-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Candi: Are you like, scared of snow or what, push me?" class="wp-image-5872" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then tried to sell me a checkered shirt for 2,250 bells. I know she&amp;#8217;s a mouse, but she&amp;#8217;s asking for a lot of cheddar! I declined the offer, and she said she&amp;#8217;ll just toss the shirt instead. (And yet she wouldn&amp;#8217;t give it to me for free.) That&amp;#8217;s Candi for you.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-candi-toss-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Candi: That's too bad. I guess I'll just toss it, push me." class="wp-image-5873" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Marcy was less concerned with ripping me off, and more focused on the snow. She even thought it was romantic.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-marcy-romantic-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Marcy: Forest in the snow... ...Don't you think it's, like, so romantic, young 'un?" class="wp-image-5874" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Puck seemed glad that the snow didn&amp;#8217;t keep me from exploring.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-puck-exploring-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Puck: Hey, evening, there. It keeps getting colder and colder, but does it stop your exploring, Jeff? No!" class="wp-image-5875" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m not exactly sure what I would be exploring, though. I&amp;#8217;ve been in this town for so long that I think I know every inch of it pretty well by now. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-puck-imitate-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Puck: I'd like to imitate that attitude, brrrrrrrrr! But I probably won't." class="wp-image-5876" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And the snow just made Hank want to pop some popcorn. 🍿 It&amp;#8217;s nice seeing all the villagers&amp;#8217; reactions to the snow. ❄️&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-hank-popping-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Hank: This snow just doesn't show signs of stopping! Too bad I don't have any corn for popping, huh!" class="wp-image-5877" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found Gulliver down on the beach again, and he gave me a matryoshka this time.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-gulliver-games-sm-300x231.jpg" alt="Gulliver: I, uh, guess I stayed up too late last night playing video games... I mean, fighting with my shipmates!" class="wp-image-5878" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Right&amp;#8230;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve recently posted a video showing the best of my GameCube Moments clips from episodes 11-20. Check it out if you&amp;#8217;d like! It&amp;#8217;s a nice trip down memory lane, as some of these clips date back to 2018 and 2019!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing - Best of GameCube Moments Vol. 2" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qOQp_QzmxeM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy the snow in your Animal Crossing towns, and Happy Holidays! 🎄&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2024/12/16/snow-reactions/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-16T19:06:50-05:00"&gt;December 16, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-16T19:06:51-05:00"&gt;December 16, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ac-peanut2024-gone-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Noodle Salads - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/14/noodle-salads/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/14/noodle-salads/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Dec 2024 04:13:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13150" class="post-13150 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Noodle Salads&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Snow now covers in the ground in Animal Crossing, and I decided to record a new gameplay session video when I played yesterday. Here is that video if you&amp;#8217;re interested&amp;#8230;or you can keep scrolling down to get to today&amp;#8217;s highlights.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe title="Animal Crossing: City Folk - December Gameplay Session (ACCF) 30+ mins." width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/iXwpEhPwElo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I won&amp;#8217;t post all of what happened in the video here in the blog, but I will share just this one screenshot of me having some coffee in the Roost.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8096-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="After drinking coffee at the Roost: This blend has the aroma and mystery of a tropical island. It's like my taste buds took a vacation!" class="wp-image-13152" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, a fishing tournament was underway. Ruby told me that she was currently in 1st place, with her 44.4-inch sea bass.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/accf-ruby444sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Ruby: Woo! A 44.4-incher!" class="wp-image-13159" sizes="(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8097-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Ruby: Guess what, li'l guy! My sea bass made the top of the chart!" class="wp-image-13153" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She was standing out on the dead end, and it&amp;#8217;s actually pretty rare for me to find anyone up there!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After making my rounds, I did a little fishing. But I was mostly just finding octopi&amp;#8230;and one squid, which Chip likes to chop up and put in his noodle salads! 🤢&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8098-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Chip: I like chopping up squid for little bouncy, floaty bits in my noodle salads! Num! Nyuuuk nyuk nyuk nyuk!" class="wp-image-13154" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I eventually caught a sea bass, but it was still much smaller than Ruby&amp;#8217;s catch. I ultimately gave up and shut off the game for the rest of the afternoon. But I did return later for the results. Ruby&amp;#8217;s catch hung on, and she was the official winner. Congrats, Ruby!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8099-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Chip: ruby from here in Forest! Solid fishing! But not so much for you. Nyuuk nyuk!" class="wp-image-13155" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After making a quick delivery to Punchy (from Mint), I finished up my night at the Roost. I asked K.K. Slider for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Western&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8100-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="One-eyed Jeff enjoys a show at the Roost." class="wp-image-13156" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Did any of you participate in the tourney? If so, I hope you had better luck than I did! I&amp;#8217;ll be back with more next week; hope to see you then! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/14/noodle-salads/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-14T23:13:11-05:00"&gt;December 14, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-14T23:34:17-05:00"&gt;December 14, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8096-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Snow Luck - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/14/snow-luck/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/14/snow-luck/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Dec 2024 03:00:33 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8495" class="post-8495 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Snow Luck&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, Pascal popped up out of the ocean and started talking about Cloud Nine. Or at least, he was wondering what was wrong with Clouds 1-8. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/pascal-cloud9-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: What's with the first eight clouds? Are they sorta good, but nothing to write home about, or what?" class="wp-image-8497" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He gave me a pearl in exchange for my scallop.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, Static asked me if I had an ant on me! I sure hope not! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/static-ant-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Static: Would you happen to have an ant on you?" class="wp-image-8498" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Yikes! Get it off, get it off! 😆&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But seriously, he just wanted to buy an ant from me for 120 bells. Sure, no problem.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As of Wednesday, snow now covers the ground in Animal Crossing games. I attempted my first &lt;s&gt;snowman&lt;/s&gt; snowboy of the season yesterday, but it didn&amp;#8217;t go well. He wasn&amp;#8217;t happy with how he turned out.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snowman2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Snowboy: Almost! So, so close." class="wp-image-8499" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I tried again tonight, and I had the same result. If you include City Folk, I&amp;#8217;m now 0-for-3 in snowmen this season so far! They&amp;#8217;re all giving me the cold shoulder! I know I&amp;#8217;m out of practice, but still, that&amp;#8217;s pretty bad. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snowman2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="My 2nd snowman of the season, which was also not quite perfect." class="wp-image-8500" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I figured that tonight would be a good &lt;s&gt;knight&lt;/s&gt; night to finally change out of my Halloween costume. So I put on my Elf outfit for the holidays.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/elf2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Jeff dressing up as Buddy the Elf for the holiday season." class="wp-image-8501" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday night, Wisp gave me a vintage TV tray. &lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, I returned a lost item to Static. He rewarded me with a flower sweater.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Calypso&amp;#8221; for me and June.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="393" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kk-121424sm-191x150.jpg" alt="K.K. Slider performs for June and Jeff." class="wp-image-8502" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;By the way, I&amp;#8217;ll probably be posting the next New Horizons Moments video sometime next week. See you soon!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/14/snow-luck/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2024-12-14T22:00:33-05:00"&gt;December 14, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/pascal-cloud9-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
